If a chiropractor fails for any reason to renew the license of the chiropractor, the Board shall reinstate the license if the chiropractor:
Applies to the Board for reinstatement of the license within 5 years after the license expires;
Meets the renewal requirements of § 3-308 of this subtitle;
Pays to the Board the reinstatement fee set by the Board; and
Passes the law and regulations portion of the Board's examination.
